<b>三脱門</b>(sān tuō mén)　“the three gates of emancipation”　<span class="xr">Cf. <a href="bword://八解門">八解門</a>(bā jiě mén), <a href="bword://八脱門">八脱門</a>(bā tuō mén), <a href="bword://解脱門">解脱門</a>(jiě tuō mén), <a href="bword://脱門">脱門</a>(tuō mén); </span><p style="margin-left:3em; text-indent:-1em;">not found at <a href="bword://HD">HD</a>.  1.233.; not found at <a href="bword://DK">DK</a>.  1.165.; </p><p style="margin-left:3em; text-indent:-2em;">63a22.(<i>bodhisattva</i>s)分別空慧、無相(←想)、無願，起(<i>v.l.</i> 超)<span style="color: #8B0000">三</span><span style="color: #8B0000">脱</span><span style="color: #8B0000">門</span>，至三達智，無去、來、今現在之想，開化黎庶，使了本無(p)</p><p style="margin-left:3em; text-indent:-1em;"><a href="bword://K">K</a>. 3.3-; not found at  <a href="bword://L">L</a>. 2a8; </p>

